# React & TanStack Patterns

## React

- Prefer **function components** with hooks; align with `src/providers/*` (context) and `src/components/song-mode/*` (feature UI).
- Keep **shared state** in providers or lifted state where the codebase already does; avoid new global singletons unless necessary.
- Use **TypeScript** types from `#/lib/song-mode/types` and related modules—do not duplicate domain shapes ad hoc.

## TanStack Router

- Add and edit routes under **`src/routes/`** using **`createFileRoute`** (see `src/routes/__root.tsx`, `src/routes/index.tsx`, `src/routes/songs.$songId.tsx`).
- Use **`<Link>`**, **`useNavigate`**, **`useMatchRoute`** from `@tanstack/react-router` consistently with existing components.
- **`src/routeTree.gen.ts`** is generated by the TanStack tooling—do not edit by hand to register routes.
- For **tests** that render routed UI, **`vi.mock("@tanstack/react-router", ...)`** is an established pattern (see existing `*.test.tsx` files).

## Testing (Vitest + Testing Library)

- Tests live next to code: **`src/**/*.test.ts`** / **`src/**/*.test.tsx`** (see `vitest.config.ts`).
- Default Vitest environment is **node**; for components that need DOM APIs, add **`// @vitest-environment jsdom`** as the first line (matches existing song-mode tests).
- Mock router hooks when asserting navigation or route-dependent UI; keep mocks minimal and aligned with `@testing-library/react` usage elsewhere in the repo.

## Knip (dead code & dependencies)

- Run **`pnpm knip`** (or **`pnpm verify`**) after dependency or export changes. Vite + Vitest plugins supply entry patterns; [`knip.json`](knip.json) aligns **`#/*`** with `./src/*` so alias imports resolve.
- Prefer **fixing** unused exports and dependencies over suppressing. Use **`/** @public */`** on intentional library exports when Knip should ignore them (see [Knip JSDoc tags](https://knip.dev/reference/jsdoc-tsdoc-tags)).
